From 82f109c06766adf4db4ad6cccff2cd6712bec115 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Tamizh Chelvam Raja <quic_tamizhr@quicinc.com>
Date: Thu, 17 Apr 2025 15:54:02 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM:CP:DP:ath12k: Add 4addr AP/STA mode support

Ath12k FW requires peer parameter WMI_PEER_USE_4ADDR to be set for
4-addr peers allowing 4-address frame transmission to those peers.
Add ath12k driver callback for sta_set_4addr() to queue new workq
set_4addr_wk only once based on boolean, use_4addr_set. sta_set_4addr()
will be called during 4-addr STA association cases
applicable for both AP and STA modes.

Below changes done to enable the WDS offload support for
ethernet offload case

* Avoid disabling hardware WDS Learning support
* Set WMI_VDEV_PARAM_AP_ENABLE_NAWDS param for the vdev
  whenver 4addr station is connected. This param needs to be
  set for 4addr multicast traffic support.

Changes are done to check WMI_SERVICE_WDS_NULL_FRAME_SUPPORT service bit
set to know that WDS null packet feature is supported by firmware.
If WDS null frame is supported by firmware, send resource config flag2
WMI_RSRC_CFG_FLAGS2_WDS_NULL_FRAME_SUPPORT(bit 22) as set to acknowledge
firmware that host is using WDS null frame feature. With this
firmware will handover the 4addr NULL frame to host for processing
and creating AP_VLAN interface.

Signed-off-by: Tamizh Chelvam Raja <quic_tamizhr@quicinc.com>
